1
00:01:37,159 --> 00:01:37,840
Feifei.

2
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,560
Remember this.

3
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,319
In the future,

4
00:01:41,599 --> 00:01:43,519
you'll encounter all sorts of things.

5
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:45,079
No matter what,

6
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:46,599
you must stay brave.

7
00:01:46,959 --> 00:01:47,599
Understand?

8
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:48,599
Okay.

9
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:53,719
And what about you?

10
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:57,519
Will you be brave too?

11
00:02:05,159 --> 00:02:05,799
Oh, right.

12
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:08,120
There's someone right now

13
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,520
you need to go see immediately.

14
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,319
Nah, forget it.

15
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:13,120
What do you mean "forget it"?

16
00:02:13,319 --> 00:02:14,560
Go on! Come on.

17
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,000
Go right now.

18
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:16,520
Right now.

19
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,759
Alright.

20
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,840
Be brave!

21
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,639
Feifei.

22
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,639
What's up? Sneaking around.

23
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,439
Are you looking for me or not?

24
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,000
I...

25
00:03:01,719 --> 00:03:03,400
You, you, you, you...

26
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:04,840
What's wrong?

27
00:03:05,199 --> 00:03:05,879
It's not that.

28
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:11,719
You know about me and Uncle Ma, right?

29
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,960
You and Uncle Ma didn't have a falling out, right?

30
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,280
No.

31
00:03:19,639 --> 00:03:20,759
We're good.

32
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,840
He and I,

33
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,360
we can talk about anything.

34
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,400
That's good then.

35
00:03:26,719 --> 00:03:27,560
So...

36
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,039
This matter is...

37
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,280
behind us.

38
00:03:31,479 --> 00:03:32,280
Behind us.

39
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,759
Maybe I still need some time.

40
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:38,199
But it's fine, it's my own issue.

41
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,719
I just hope

42
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,560
we can get along like before.

43
00:03:42,199 --> 00:03:42,840
Sis.

44
00:03:43,719 --> 00:03:45,000
You don't need to feel pressured.

45
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,840
Or avoid me.

46
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,840
Or be shy.

47
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:50,000
You little rascal, turning the tables on me!

48
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,639
You're the one who's been avoiding me!

49
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,800
Yeah, yeah.

50
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,560
Alright, don't be sad.

51
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,000
Heartbreak

52
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,000
is a required course for growing up.

53
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,159
You'll get used to it.

54
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,759
Sis, right now the whole Baofang Hutong,

55
00:04:02,759 --> 00:04:04,280
even Auntie Zhao is comforting me.

56
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,319
I really don't need one more person.

57
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,080
Fine.

58
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:06,840
I was just afraid

59
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,120
of losing a little brother like you.

60
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:11,000
I'm late, Sis.

61
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,039
Sis, I really have to go.

62
00:04:12,039 --> 00:04:13,800
Otherwise you really will lose me.

63
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,360
Go on.

64
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,400
Pay attention in class.

65
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:15,840
Bye.

66
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:16,399
Bye.

67
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:33,120
So where exactly is this place?

68
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,079
Don't ask so many questions.

69
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:35,040
I've got it all arranged.

70
00:04:35,319 --> 00:04:36,360
Just follow me.

71
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,839
Always so mysterious and secretive.

72
00:04:41,839 --> 00:04:43,319
Chunsheng, not bad!

73
00:04:43,319 --> 00:04:44,839
A Harley Street Glide.

74
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:46,160
Chrome luggage rack.

75
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,079
Fairing.

76
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:47,959
Upgraded suspension.

77
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:49,519
This bike is sweet.

78
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,360
Wow, you know your stuff.

79
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,519
That's about the extent of my knowledge.

80
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:53,800
Talking like a real expert.

81
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,199
Big bro.

82
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:54,720
Really nice!

83
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,519
Uncle Wang.

84
00:04:55,519 --> 00:04:56,360
Whose bike is this?

85
00:04:56,519 --> 00:04:57,319
Mine.

86
00:04:57,959 --> 00:04:58,759
What about the old one?

87
00:04:58,759 --> 00:04:59,800
Why'd you get a new one?

88
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,839
The old one's ancient, I'm keeping it as a collectible.

89
00:05:01,839 --> 00:05:03,120
This one's brand new.

90
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,720
I plan to take your auntie out on a trip.

91
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,120
Then, then what about Feifei?

92
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,319
Feifei's about to

93
00:05:07,319 --> 00:05:08,519
start college soon, right?

94
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,079
We need to get used to being a couple again.

95
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:12,160
So Feifei's on his own.

96
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:12,800
And the restaurant...

97
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,800
The restaurant is your responsibility too.

98
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,360
Alright then.

99
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,800
Wife, let's go!

100
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,560
Stop rushing me!

101
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:21,800
I need to sort things out at the restaurant first.

102
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,600
Auntie.

103
00:05:22,839 --> 00:05:24,839
Sis, you look twenty years younger!

104
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:27,079
That's a bit of an exaggeration.

105
00:05:27,079 --> 00:05:29,160
More like ten years or so.

106
00:05:29,759 --> 00:05:31,160
Auntie, if you dressed like this every day,

107
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,319
Uncle Wang would be totally smitten.

108
00:05:33,759 --> 00:05:35,560
Would your Uncle Wang dare look at anyone else now?

109
00:05:36,759 --> 00:05:38,600
Let's go, beautiful.

110
00:05:40,839 --> 00:05:42,600
So sweet.

111
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,800
Let's go.

112
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,519
Wow, this gear is really something.

113
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:47,160
We're off!

114
00:05:47,319 --> 00:05:48,399
Be safe!

115
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,279
Have fun!

116
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:50,160
Old Wang, shirking his duties.

117
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:50,800
Off to be romantic.

118
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,519
Watch your leg swinging on!

119
00:05:51,519 --> 00:05:52,120
Be careful, Auntie!

120
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,839
Have your fun, but be safe, okay?

121
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:56,120
Take a picture!

122
00:05:58,839 --> 00:05:59,800
Safe travels!

123
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,319
Go!

124
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:00,959
We're leaving!

125
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,639
Fun, riding a motorcycle like this.

126
00:06:43,639 --> 00:06:45,519
What a gas guzzler.

127
00:06:58,639 --> 00:06:59,519
It's quite spacious.

128
00:07:00,879 --> 00:07:02,439
This place is really nice.

129
00:07:03,639 --> 00:07:05,160
But it must be expensive, right?

130
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,480
I can't afford it.

131
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,920
Actually,

132
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,720
Actually... Stop with the "actually"!

133
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,360
I told you, I have principles.

134
00:07:13,639 --> 00:07:15,879
I have to handle everything for this photo exhibition myself.

135
00:07:17,839 --> 00:07:19,560
Actually, it's not as expensive as you think.

136
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:20,879
You can afford it.

137
00:07:22,399 --> 00:07:23,560
The owner here,

138
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:25,319
also grew up in Beijing.

139
00:07:25,639 --> 00:07:27,160
He lives abroad now.

140
00:07:27,519 --> 00:07:28,639
When he heard

141
00:07:28,639 --> 00:07:30,920
you wanted to hold an exhibition about Beijing's ecology,

142
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,959
he got really excited.

143
00:07:32,279 --> 00:07:33,519
So he gave us a discount.

144
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,199
Really?

145
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:38,360
You must have blackmailed him or something.

146
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,920
Honestly, Xiaoqi arranged it.

147
00:07:44,879 --> 00:07:45,519
Really.

148
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:47,319
The day he came to see me,

149
00:07:47,319 --> 00:07:48,399
he had already made the arrangements.

150
00:07:48,639 --> 00:07:50,079
He told me not to tell you.

151
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:52,160
And insisted on taking the credit for it.

152
00:07:54,879 --> 00:07:57,399
That little punk is actually not so bad.

153
00:08:02,959 --> 00:08:04,519
I got something for you.

154
00:08:14,879 --> 00:08:15,839
What is it?

155
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,319
Well?

156
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,799
You remembered?

157
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:34,879
I remember.

158
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,120
Come in.

159
00:09:09,639 --> 00:09:10,279
Hello.

160
00:09:10,279 --> 00:09:10,879
Hello.

161
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:12,919
Alright, have a seat.

162
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:13,720
Thank you, thank you.

163
00:09:20,039 --> 00:09:21,120
Tong Qiu, right?

164
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:26,240
I heard you were fired.

165
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:33,120
And for inappropriate conduct with the opposite sex.

166
00:10:27,919 --> 00:10:28,840
Mr. Tong,

167
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,480
your background check did not pass.

168
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,360
Very regrettable.

169
00:10:31,519 --> 00:10:33,480
Sorry. We look forward to future cooperation.

170
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:36,120
Thank you.

171
00:10:36,399 --> 00:10:37,159
Goodbye.

172
00:11:37,879 --> 00:11:38,639
Brother Ming.

173
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:39,879
Xiao Tong.

174
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:46,080
You're here to... to hire people.

175
00:11:50,159 --> 00:11:51,159
Interviewing?

176
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:54,360
You... your side...

177
00:11:54,519 --> 00:11:55,639
had some issues.

178
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,799
I can... can understand. This, this...

179
00:11:59,799 --> 00:12:03,399
It's tough to achieve good performance these days.

180
00:12:07,559 --> 00:12:09,360
If the heart is there, the dream is there.

181
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,960
At worst, you just start over.

182
00:12:16,559 --> 00:12:17,519
Going to the restroom.

183
00:12:17,879 --> 00:12:18,320
Well...

184
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,440
You go ahead then.

185
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,159
I'm not in a hurry.

186
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,240
Then I'll go first.

187
00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:31,519
So awkward.

188
00:12:35,279 --> 00:12:36,559
A terrifying coincidence.

189
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:20,360
Hello?

190
00:13:20,919 --> 00:13:21,720
Lian Bao.

191
00:13:22,039 --> 00:13:24,159
Have you signed Yuanyuan's immigration consent form?

192
00:13:25,919 --> 00:13:28,279
I was just about to. What's up?

193
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:29,559
Don't sign it yet.

194
00:13:48,799 --> 00:13:51,320
Make a big scene, then quietly leave.

195
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:54,720
Easier said than done.

196
00:13:55,759 --> 00:13:57,679
Too much reluctance and concern.

197
00:13:58,039 --> 00:13:59,759
Prevent me from leaving quietly.

198
00:14:00,519 --> 00:14:01,919
Let alone actually leaving.

199
00:14:03,919 --> 00:14:05,480
Since things can't be spoken plainly,

200
00:14:05,879 --> 00:14:07,840
leaving some hope is better for everyone.

201
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:09,960
All I can do

202
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:12,480
is try to settle everything properly.

203
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:13,879
And then...

204
00:14:14,919 --> 00:14:16,480
quietly await that day's arrival.

205
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,440
Mom, Dad, I'll hang up now.

206
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,840
Okay, okay, okay.

207
00:15:08,919 --> 00:15:09,480
Alright.

208
00:15:09,639 --> 00:15:11,720
Bye, bye, bye.

209
00:15:13,639 --> 00:15:15,039
You're useless too.

210
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:17,840
Can't even compete with those young kids at work.

211
00:15:18,159 --> 00:15:19,399
Who pays the mortgage?

212
00:15:19,559 --> 00:15:20,600
A grown man,

213
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,120
doesn't know to focus on his career.

214
00:15:25,039 --> 00:15:26,440
Our company

215
00:15:26,559 --> 00:15:28,240
has a transfer opportunity.

216
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,440
To Xi'an.

217
00:15:29,879 --> 00:15:31,759
Salary increases by fifty percent.

218
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:33,440
Not coming back for a year?

219
00:15:33,559 --> 00:15:35,320
That... wouldn't work.

220
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,799
But this time is different.

221
00:15:37,039 --> 00:15:38,799
It's not just a salary increase.

222
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,080
There's a chance to become a director.

223
00:15:46,559 --> 00:15:49,840
Right now, the competition for the director position

224
00:15:50,039 --> 00:15:51,639
is extremely fierce.

225
00:15:52,039 --> 00:15:54,320
And headquarters' idea is that

226
00:15:54,519 --> 00:15:57,240
if I stay in Xi'an for another year,

227
00:15:57,879 --> 00:15:58,879
it's more secure.

228
00:15:58,879 --> 00:16:00,039
Stay another year?

229
00:16:04,159 --> 00:16:05,519
Your key performance indicators for the past six months

230
00:16:05,519 --> 00:16:06,600
haven't been properly met.

231
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,600
Daily reports, monthly, quarterly, annual reports...

232
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,720
Look at the garbage you wrote yourself.

233
00:16:11,559 --> 00:16:12,799
Don't be angry.

234
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:15,320
Yes, it's my problem.

235
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,799
It really is my problem.

236
00:16:18,799 --> 00:16:19,679
Honey.

237
00:16:20,039 --> 00:16:22,600
This promotion probably isn't happening this time.

238
00:16:22,919 --> 00:16:25,480
And the next promotion probably won't happen either.

239
00:16:25,799 --> 00:16:26,720
I'm sorry.

240
00:16:26,919 --> 00:16:28,320
What a mess.

241
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:42,679
Why do you think everything is so simple?

242
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,200
This matter of yours is unclear.

243
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,600
Would another bank dare hire you?

244
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,799
Yes, yes, yes.

245
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,480
Don't... don't get worked up.

246
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:53,440
Besides,

247
00:16:54,399 --> 00:16:55,919
those two clients of yours,

248
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:58,639
did you get them through your own ability?

249
00:17:17,039 --> 00:17:18,559
Don't you think it's strange?

250
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,079
Before, Yuanyuan said she didn't want to immigrate.

251
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,839
Now she suddenly changed her mind.

252
00:17:24,519 --> 00:17:25,640
Kids...

253
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:28,680
Maybe Yuanyuan just feels sorry for her old dad,

254
00:17:28,799 --> 00:17:30,279
trying to cheer me up for a bit.

255
00:17:30,359 --> 00:17:32,000
The way you are as a father...

256
00:17:32,119 --> 00:17:33,079
You have so little faith

257
00:17:33,079 --> 00:17:34,599
in Yuanyuan's feelings for you.

258
00:17:35,039 --> 00:17:36,039
What do you mean?

259
00:17:36,039 --> 00:17:38,279
Yuanyuan actually didn't tell you the truth at all.

260
00:17:38,559 --> 00:17:39,559
You know how it is,

261
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:42,119
kids can't keep secrets.

262
00:17:42,359 --> 00:17:44,319
She told Xuanxuan about it.

263
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,079
Xuanxuan told me.

264
00:17:46,519 --> 00:17:48,599
She said she doesn't want to go abroad at all.

265
00:17:48,759 --> 00:17:50,839
Hu Nana told her to say that to you.

266
00:18:04,039 --> 00:18:04,880
Jenny

267
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:07,039
Do you love Daddy?

268
00:18:07,079 --> 00:18:07,839
Yes.

269
00:18:09,279 --> 00:18:11,039
Daddy is in trouble now.

270
00:18:11,039 --> 00:18:12,480
Do you want to help him?

271
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:13,039
Yes.

272
00:18:16,599 --> 00:18:18,079
You know what, Jenny?

273
00:18:18,359 --> 00:18:21,480
Uncle Kevin is Daddy's investor.

274
00:18:21,759 --> 00:18:23,359
If it weren't for Uncle Kevin,

275
00:18:23,359 --> 00:18:25,000
Daddy wouldn't have a job.

276
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,119
But now,

277
00:18:26,119 --> 00:18:28,519
Uncle Kevin wants you and Mommy

278
00:18:28,519 --> 00:18:30,279
to move abroad together.

279
00:18:30,759 --> 00:18:32,359
If you don't want to go,

280
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,279
Uncle Kevin will be unhappy.

281
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:36,240
And if Uncle Kevin is unhappy,

282
00:18:36,319 --> 00:18:37,640
Daddy will lose his job.

283
00:18:37,799 --> 00:18:39,519
What should I do then?

284
00:18:39,519 --> 00:18:41,599
I don't want Daddy to be sad.

285
00:18:43,279 --> 00:18:44,319
So,

286
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:45,839
you need to tell Daddy

287
00:18:45,839 --> 00:18:49,200
that you want to move abroad with Mommy.

288
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:52,799
